er while ensuring valid JSON output and summarizing risks appropriately.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core resolves with only Kotlin/coroutines runtime dependencies and includes built-in property sources, default decoders, ServiceLoader metadata, and a Java properties parser, so meaningful core coverage is reachable without extra Maven modules, Docker, or global environment setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use core-only APIs such as MapPropertySource, PropertySource.string(..., \\\"properties\\\"), PropertySource.resource/path with .properties/.props files, ConfigLoaderBuilder.empty()/default(), default decoders, preprocessors, resolvers, and data-class decoding. If testing SystemPropertiesPropertySource, set properties with the documented config.override.* prefix inside the test and clear them afterwards. No environment variable or system property is required globally.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation examples often use YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON, but those formats require optional hoplite-* format modules; avoid those formats unless a later workflow deliberately adds the matching dependency.\",\n    \"EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource reads System.getenv(), which is hard to mutate safely in tests; prefer MapPropertySource or explicit constructor-injected maps where possible.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_091fc2914c59a575016a40b88ce3fc8193a7cb54c4721de1b1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4783, "output": 1193, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44888, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782626424308, "responseId": "resp_091fc2914c59a575016a40b878ca90819395f5b2d8b4562fc0"}, "toolResults": []}
